## Vaultwarden - Password Storage

### Access

- URL: https://vault.lab.local - Master Password: Stored offline in secure location - Usage: Human access to all passwords

### Organization Structure

Folders:

Homelab Infrastructure - FreeIPA Admin - PostgreSQL (Gitea Database) - MariaDB Root - MariaDB (WordPress Database User) - Proxmox Host - Ansible Vault Password - SSH Keys (Secure Note)

Homelab Services - Gitea Admin - WordPress Admin - Grafana Admin - Portainer Admin - DokuWiki Admin - Uptime Kuma Admin - Vaultwarden Admin (self-reference)

Personal - FreeIPA User Account (jireland) - Personal email accounts

Work (future use)

### Password Standards

Generation: - Minimum length: 32 characters - Complexity: Numbers, uppercase, lowercase, special characters - Generated using Vaultwarden's built-in generator - No dictionary words or patterns

Rotation Schedule: - Database passwords: Every 90 days - Service admin passwords: Every 180 days - FreeIPA admin: Every 90 days - SSH keys: Every 365 days - Infrastructure credentials: Every 90 days

Entry Template:

Each Vaultwarden entry includes: - Name: Service/System identifier - Username: Account username - Password: Generated strong password - URL: Service URL (if applicable) - Notes: Purpose, location, last rotated date, usage instructions

## Ansible Vault - Infrastructure Secrets

### Encrypted Vault File

Location: `/opt/ansible/vars/vault.yml`

Encryption: Ansible Vault (AES256)

Vault Password: Stored in Vaultwarden (“Ansible Vault Password” entry)

Contents:

```yaml — # Database Passwords vault_postgres_password: “encrypted_value_here” vault_mariadb_root_password: “encrypted_value_here” vault_mariadb_wordpress_password: “encrypted_value_here”

# Service Admin Passwords vault_grafana_admin_password: “encrypted_value_here” vault_gitea_admin_password: “encrypted_value_here”

# Infrastructure vault_freeipa_admin_password: “encrypted_value_here” vault_proxmox_password: “encrypted_value_here” ```

### Accessing Vault

View contents:

```bash ansible-vault view /opt/ansible/vars/vault.yml # Enter vault password when prompted ```

Edit vault:

```bash ansible-vault edit /opt/ansible/vars/vault.yml # Opens in nano (configured via EDITOR variable) # Make changes, save, exit ```

Encrypt existing file:

```bash ansible-vault encrypt /opt/ansible/vars/plaintext.yml ```

Decrypt to file (not recommended):

```bash ansible-vault decrypt /opt/ansible/vars/vault.yml # Creates plaintext file - dangerous! ```

### Automated Access

Vault password file: `/opt/ansible/.vault_pass`

Permissions: 0600 (owner read/write only)

Purpose: Allows Ansible playbooks to decrypt vault.yml automatically without prompting

Configuration: Referenced in `/opt/ansible/ansible.cfg`:

```ini [defaults] vault_password_file = /opt/ansible/.vault_pass ```

Security: Protected by .gitignore to prevent accidental commits

## Environment Files (.env)

### Generation

Environment files are automatically generated from Ansible Vault using playbook:

```bash ansible-playbook /opt/ansible/playbooks/generate-env-files.yml ```

This playbook: 1. Reads encrypted vault.yml 2. Decrypts passwords using vault password file 3. Generates .env files on target hosts with plaintext passwords 4. Sets secure permissions (0600) 5. Adds .env to .gitignore if not already present

### Locations

- apps.lab.local: `/opt/docker/.env` - mntr.lab.local: `/opt/docker/.env`

### File Format

```bash # Generated from Ansible Vault - DO NOT EDIT MANUALLY # Last generated: 2026-03-30T18:30:00Z

# PostgreSQL (Gitea) POSTGRES_PASSWORD=actual_password_here

# MariaDB MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=actual_password_here MYSQL_PASSWORD=actual_password_here

# WordPress WORDPRESS_DB_PASSWORD=actual_password_here ```

### Permissions and Security

- File permissions: 0600 (owner read/write only) - Owner: jireland - Group: jireland - Protected by: .gitignore (never committed to version control)

### Docker Compose Integration

Docker Compose automatically reads .env files from the same directory as docker-compose.yml:

```yaml services:

postgres:
  environment:
    POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}

```

Variable substitution happens at runtime when containers start.

## Docker Compose Configuration

### Using Environment Variables

Instead of hardcoded passwords:

```yaml # BAD - hardcoded password environment:

POSTGRES_PASSWORD: "MySecretPassword123"

```

Use environment variables from .env:

```yaml # GOOD - references .env file environment:

POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}

```

Docker Compose automatically: 1. Reads .env file from same directory 2. Substitutes ${VARIABLE} with actual values 3. Passes environment variables to containers

Verification:

```bash # View actual values that will be used (without starting containers) docker compose config | grep PASSWORD

# Should show actual passwords, not ${VARIABLES} ```

## Password Rotation Workflow

### Step-by-Step Process

1. Generate New Password:

In Vaultwarden: - Edit entry (e.g., “PostgreSQL - Gitea Database”) - Click “Generate Password” - Set length 32, enable all character types - Save new password

2. Update Ansible Vault:

```bash ansible-vault edit /opt/ansible/vars/vault.yml # Update password variable # Save and exit ```

3. Update Password in Service:

For PostgreSQL: ```bash docker exec -it postgres psql -U postgres ALTER USER jireland WITH PASSWORD 'NEW_PASSWORD'; \q ```

For MariaDB: ```bash docker exec -it mariadb mysql -u root -p ALTER USER 'username'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'NEW_PASSWORD'; ALTER USER 'username'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'NEW_PASSWORD'; FLUSH PRIVILEGES; EXIT; ```

4. Regenerate .env Files:

```bash ansible-playbook /opt/ansible/playbooks/generate-env-files.yml ```

5. Restart Affected Containers:

```bash cd /opt/docker docker compose restart service_name ```

6. Verify Service Functionality:

```bash # Check logs for authentication errors docker logs service_name –tail 50

# Test service access curl -I https://service.lab.local ```

7. Update Metadata in Vaultwarden:

Edit entry notes to include: - Last rotated: [current date] - Next rotation: [date + 90/180 days]

